# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# HOW TO USE THESE FILES:
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# 1. Create your GitHub repository
# 2. Clone it locally
# 3. Copy all files to appropriate directories
# 4. Install dependencies:
#    pip install -r requirements.txt

# 5. Set up environment:
#    cp .env.example .env
#    # Edit .env with your settings

# 6. Run the agent:
#    python groq_colab_agent_complete.py

# 7. Or using Docker:
#    docker-compose up -d

# 8. Run tests:
#    make test

# 9. Format code:
#    make format

# 10. Push to GitHub:
#     git add .
#     git commit -m "Initial commit: Groq Colab Agent"
#     git push origin main
